                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-300-off1531 t18300916-300-victim2461"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>GEORGE ALLEN. I am <rs id="t18300916-300-viclabel1533" type="occupation">groom</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-300-victim2461 t18300916-300-viclabel1533"></join> to Captain Osborne; the prisoner is a <rs id="t18300916-300-deflabel1534" type="occupation">groom</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-300-defend2459 t18300916-300-deflabel1534"></join>, and lodged in the same house with me for about two months - he told me he owed a horse-dealer some money, and was compelled to pay it, but he had not enough; he asked me to lend him some - I said I could not, but would let him have my watch to deposit with the ostler - I went with him, and saw the ostler's wife receive the watch; he was to bring it back to me immediately it was returned - I never permitted him to pawn it; I went to his master's stables to assist him, and left my jacket and overalls in the room over the stables: I had not lent them to him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you not give me these things? A. Never; I did not authorize you to pawn any thing - I never pawned the watch myself; I asked him where the duplicates were - he said he had left them at a coffee-shop for 3s.; I gave him 3s. to get them - he returned, and said the man was not at home; I slept with you one or two nights, but you did not support me - you gave me a breakfast when I helped you work.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-300-person2462">
                  JOHN 
                  BALLAM
               <interp inst="t18300916-300-person2462" type="surname" value="BALLAM"></interp>
